results.name: Decimal expansion of Product_{p prime} (1 - 2/p^3).
comment: The asymptotic density of the sequence of cubefree numbers k such that k+1 is also cubefree (A340152) (Carlitz, 1932).
link: Leonard Carlitz, On a problem in additive arithmetic (II), The Quarterly Journal of Mathematics, Vol. os-3, No. 1 (1932), pp. 273-290.
mathematica: $MaxExtraPrecision = 500; m = 500; c = LinearRecurrence[{0, 0, 2}, {0, 0, -6}, m]; RealDigits[Exp[NSum[Indexed[c, n]*(PrimeZetaP[n])/n, {n, 2, m}, NSumTerms -> m, WorkingPrecision -> m]], 10, 100][[1]]
